==English==

===Etymology===
Possibly a contraction of [[spastic]] (as a term of abuse), or from the phrase "Spack off!!" spoken by Tom Baker playing Dr. Who in 1974's ''Genesis Of The Daleks''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{cattag|slang|pejoratives}} A [[clumsy]], [[foolish]], or [[mentally]] [[deficient]] person.
#:*"You spilt beer on your shirt, you '''spack'''!" 
<!--does not support noun sense-->
<!--#:*"'''Spack''' off!"  by Doctor Who in 1974's ''Genesis Of The Daleks''--> 

